text: Anicka Delgado (born 13 June 2002) is an Ecuadorian swimmer. She competed in the women's 50 metre butterfly and women's 100 metre freestyle events at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. In both events she did not advance to compete in the semi-finals. ==References== Category:2002 births Category:Living people Category:Ecuadorian female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Swimmers at the 2018 Summer Youth Olympics Category:Swimmers at the 2019 Pan American Games Category:Female freestyle swimmers Category:Female butterfly swimmers
